The paper focuses on using the crowd to prevent bias in machine learning data collection, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the diversity of the workers' suggestions, which relates to social and information networks (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions Amazon's Mechanical Turk, which is often used in studies related to cybernetics (cs.CY).
